From: Nicolai Stange <nstange@suse.de>
Date: Tue, 09 Jun 2026 11:35:31 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] crypto/testmgr: disallow ffdhe2048 in fips mode
References: jsc#PED-15986,bsc#1266284
Patch-mainline: Not yet, downstream provision to maintain cert validity beyond 2030.

DH with 112 bits of security strength (i.e. ffdhe2048) will be
deprecated after 2030 for FIPS. Flip ->fips_allowed for ffdhe2048 to 0.

Signed-off-by: Nicolai Stange <nstange@suse.de>

---
 crypto/testmgr.c |    2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/crypto/testmgr.c
+++ b/crypto/testmgr.c
@@ -5172,7 +5172,7 @@ static const struct alg_test_desc alg_te
 #if IS_ENABLED(CONFIG_CRYPTO_DH_RFC7919_GROUPS)
 		.alg = "ffdhe2048(dh)",
 		.test = alg_test_kpp,
-		.fips_allowed = 1,
+		.fips_allowed = 0,
 		.suite = {
 			.kpp = __VECS(ffdhe2048_dh_tv_template)
 		}
